            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I had heard very good things about the academics of Vanasthali School, Sector 3, so I visited the school for my child’s admission. Unfortunately, my perception changed completely after interacting with the receptionist, Mrs. Princi Ma’am.\n\nDuring the conversation, she repeatedly started responding before I could finish explaining my query. In a role like reception, it is important to first listen to parents carefully and then respond accordingly. Communication and patience are essential, as the reception desk is the first point of contact and forms the initial impression of the school.\n\nAt one point, she also used the phrase that “class people come here,” which I found quite inappropriate. If the school expects “class people,” then the staff should also maintain a professional and respectful standard while interacting with parents. Such an attitude raises concerns about what kind of values are being demonstrated in front of parents and children.\n\nThere was another staff member assisting her, and I found her approach much more professional and helpful. She listened patiently and addressed our queries properly.\n\nOverall, this experience left a disappointing impression, and I did not find the school environment suitable based on this interaction.",
